## What do we use RSpec for?

We use RSpec to write both unit and integration tests for Ruby code.

## Why RSpec?

When it comes to unit tests [RSpec is the most popular test framework for Ruby][ruby-toolbox], and is [recommended for Rails][gorails] .
For integration tests, there is another popular alternative to RSpec, [Cucumber][cucumber].

Many GOV.UK applications have some or all of their integration tests written in Cucumber. However, we are gradually moving away from Cucumber in favour of using RSpec, for reasons outlined in [How we write readable feature tests with RSpec][chris-zetter-blogpost].

Essentially, using RSpec for both BDD and TDD requires less of a context switch than using a separate tool for BDD.

